# Replace NA values with zeros in the Area..mm.2. column
#df_clean$FvFm[is.na(df_clean$FvFm)] <- 0

# Filter the dataframe to get data for the final timepoint (22)
final_timepoint_fvfm_df <- df_clean %>%
  filter(Timepoint == 22) %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Cross_2, SymbiontTreatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_fvfm = mean(FvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_fvfm = sd(FvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
final_timepoint_fvfm_df <- final_timepoint_fvfm_df %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Define a custom color palette
custom_colors <- c(\BxB\ = \#1f77b4\, \TxT\ = \#ff7f0e\) # Modify colors as needed

# Plot the mean area with error bars and custom colors
fvfm_plot <- ggplot(final_timepoint_fvfm_df, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_fvfm, 
                               color = Cross_2, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_fvfm - se_fvfm, ymax = mean_fvfm + se_fvfm), 
                width = 0.2) +
  scale_color_manual(values = custom_colors) +  # Apply the custom color palette
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Mean Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Mean Larval Fv/Fm at Final Timepoint (22)\) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = \right\)

fvfm_plot

# Updated area_plot with only x and y axis lines, no grid lines, and a dashed line at y = 0
fvfm_plot <- ggplot(final_timepoint_fvfm_df, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_fvfm, 
                                            color = Cross_2, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_fvfm - se_fvfm, ymax = mean_fvfm + se_fvfm), 
                width = 0.2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = \dashed\, color = \grey\) +  # Add dashed line at y = 0
  scale_color_manual(values = custom_colors) +  # Apply the custom color palette
  labs(x = \Temperature Treatment\, y = \Mean Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Mean Larval Fv/Fm at Final Timepoint (22)\) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = \right\,
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\),  # Keep x and y axis lines
    axis.ticks = element_line(color = \black\)  # Add axis ticks
  )

# Display the plot
print(fvfm_plot)

# Create inset for the above plot
# Step 1: Filter the dataframe to get data for the final timepoint (22)
final_timepoint_fvfm_df_inset <- df_clean %>%
  filter(Timepoint == 22) %>%
  group_by(Treatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_fvfm = mean(FvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_fvfm = sd(FvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
final_timepoint_fvfm_df_inset <- final_timepoint_fvfm_df_inset %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Step 2: Create the plot
mean_fvfm_plot <- ggplot(final_timepoint_fvfm_df_inset, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_fvfm)) +
  geom_point(size = 4, shape = 1, fill = NA, stroke = 1.5) +  # Adjust point size as needed
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_fvfm - se_fvfm, ymax = mean_fvfm + se_fvfm), 
                width = 0.2) +
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Mean Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Mean Larval Fv/Fm at Final Timepoint (All Crosses and Symbiont Treatments)\) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\, linewidth = 0.5)  # Keep axis lines
  )

# Step 4: Display the plot
print(mean_fvfm_plot)

# Create inset for the above plot seperated by Treatment and Symbiont treatment
# Step 1: Filter the dataframe to get data for the final timepoint (22)
final_timepoint_fvfm_df_inset2 <- df_clean %>%
  filter(Timepoint == 22) %>%
  group_by(Treatment, SymbiontTreatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_fvfm = mean(FvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_fvfm = sd(FvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
final_timepoint_fvfm_df_inset2 <- final_timepoint_fvfm_df_inset2 %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Step 2: Create the plot
mean_fvfm_plot2 <- ggplot(final_timepoint_fvfm_df_inset2, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_fvfm, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +
  geom_point(size = 4, fill = NA, stroke = 1.5) +  # Adjust point size as needed
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_fvfm - se_fvfm, ymax = mean_fvfm + se_fvfm), 
                width = 0.2) +
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Mean Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Mean Larval Fv/Fm at Final Timepoint (All Crosses and Symbiont Treatments)\) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\, linewidth = 0.5)  # Keep axis lines
  )

# Step 4: Display the plot
print(mean_fvfm_plot2)

# Combine the two plots side by side
combined_plot_mean_fvfm <- mean_fvfm_plot + mean_fvfm_plot2 + plot_layout(ncol = 2)

# Display the combined plot
print(combined_plot_mean_fvfm)

# Save the combined plot as a PNG file
ggsave(\combined_plot_mean_fvfm_inset.png\, plot = combined_plot_mean_fvfm, width = 6, height = 3, dpi = 300)

# Filter the dataframe to get data for the final timepoint (22)
final_timepoint_fvfm_df <- df_clean %>%
  filter(Timepoint == 22) %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Cross_2, SymbiontTreatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_fvfm = mean(FvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_fvfm = sd(FvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order

  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Plot the mean area with error bars and custom colors

                               color = Cross_2, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +

fvfm_plot

                                            color = Cross_2, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +

  )

       title = \Mean Larval Fv/Fm at Final Timepoint (All Crosses and Symbiont Treatments)\) +

    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines

  )

print(mean_fvfm_plot)

-->

colnames(df_clean)[32] <- \FvFm\

# Extract the fvfm at Timepoint 4 (first measurement)
fvfm_t4 <- df_clean %>%
  filter(Timepoint == 4) %>%
  select(UniqueID, FvFm) %>%
  rename(FvFmT4 = FvFm)

# Extract the fvfm at Timepoint 22 (last measurement)
fvfm_t22 <- df_clean %>%
  filter(Timepoint == 22) %>%
  select(UniqueID, FvFm) %>%
  rename(FvFmT22 = FvFm)

# Merge FvFmT4 and FvFmT22 back into the main dataframe
df_clean <- df_clean %>%
  left_join(fvfm_t4, by = \UniqueID\, relationship = \many-to-many\) %>%
  left_join(fvfm_t22, by = \UniqueID\, relationship = \many-to-many\)

# Add a small constant to FvFmT4 and FvFmT22 where values are 0
small_constant <- 0.0000000001

# Replace 0 values in FvFmT4 and FvFmT22 with the small constant
df_clean$FvFmT4 <- ifelse(df_clean$FvFmT4 == 0, small_constant, df_clean$FvFmT4)
df_clean$FvFmT22 <- ifelse(df_clean$FvFmT22 == 0, small_constant, df_clean$FvFmT22)

# Calculate the percent change
df_clean$PercChangeFvFm <- (df_clean$FvFmT22 - df_clean$FvFmT4) / df_clean$FvFmT4 * 100

df_clean <- df_clean %>%
  mutate(
    LogChangeFvFm = log(FvFmT22 / FvFmT4)  # Logarithmic change
  )

# Now df_clean has a new column 'PercChangeFvFm' representing the percent change in fvfm between Timepoint 4 and Timepoint 22

# Group by Treatment, Cross_2, and SymbiontTreatment, and calculate mean and standard error for percent change
log_change_fvfm_summary <- df_clean %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Cross_2, SymbiontTreatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_log_change = mean(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_log_change = sd(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
log_change_fvfm_summary <- log_change_fvfm_summary %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Define a custom color palette (same as before)
custom_colors <- c(\BxB\ = \#1f77b4\, \TxT\ = \#ff7f0e\)  # Modify colors as needed

# Plot the percent change in area with error bars and custom colors
log_change_fvfm_plot <- ggplot(log_change_fvfm_summary, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_log_change, 
                                                    color = Cross_2, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_log_change - se_log_change, ymax = mean_log_change + se_log_change), 
                width = 0.2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = \dashed\, color = \grey\) +  # Add dashed line at y = 0
  scale_color_manual(values = custom_colors) +  # Apply the custom color palette
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Log Change in Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Log Change in Larval Fv/Fm from Timepoint 4 to 22\) +
  ylim(-5, 15) +  # Adjust y-axis limits (change the values as needed)
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = \right\,
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\),  # Keep x and y axis lines
    axis.ticks = element_line(color = \black\)  # Add axis ticks
  )

# Display the plot
print(log_change_fvfm_plot)

# Create inset just for treatment
# Group by Treatment and calculate mean and standard error for percent change
log_change_summary2 <- df_clean %>%
  group_by(Treatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_log_change = mean(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_log_change = sd(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
log_change_summary2 <- log_change_summary2 %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Plot the percent change in area with error bars and custom colors
log_change_plot2 <- ggplot(log_change_summary2, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_log_change)) +
  geom_point(size = 4, shape = 1, stroke = 1.5) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_log_change - se_log_change, ymax = mean_log_change + se_log_change), 
                width = 0.2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = \dashed\, color = \grey\) +  # Add dashed line at y = 0
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Log Change in Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Log Change in Larval Fv/Fm from Timepoint 4 to 22\) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = \right\,
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\),  # Keep x and y axis lines
    axis.ticks = element_line(color = \black\)  # Add axis ticks
  )

# Display the plot
print(log_change_plot2)

# Create inset for treatment and symbiont treatment
# Group by Treatment and SymbiontTreatment, and calculate mean and standard error for percent change
log_change_summary3 <- df_clean %>%
  group_by(Treatment, SymbiontTreatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_log_change = mean(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_log_change = sd(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
log_change_summary3 <- log_change_summary3 %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Plot the percent change in area with error bars and custom colors
log_change_plot3 <- ggplot(log_change_summary3, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_log_change, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +
  geom_point(size = 4, stroke = 1.5) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_log_change - se_log_change, ymax = mean_log_change + se_log_change), 
                width = 0.2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = \dashed\, color = \grey\) +  # Add dashed line at y = 0
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Log Change in Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Log Change in Larval Fv/Fm from Timepoint 4 to 22\) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = \right\,
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\),  # Keep x and y axis lines
    axis.ticks = element_line(color = \black\)  # Add axis ticks
  )

# Display the plot
print(log_change_plot3)

library(patchwork)

# Combine the two plots side by side
combined_plot_log_fvfm <- log_change_plot2 + log_change_plot3 + plot_layout(ncol = 2)

# Display the combined plot
print(combined_plot_log_fvfm)

# Save the combined plot as a PNG file
ggsave(\combined_plot_log_fvfm_inset.png\, plot = combined_plot_log_fvfm, width = 6, height = 3, dpi = 300)

```r
colnames(df_clean)[32] <- \FvFm\

# Extract the fvfm at Timepoint 4 (first measurement)
fvfm_t4 <- df_clean %>%
  filter(Timepoint == 4) %>%
  select(UniqueID, FvFm) %>%
  rename(FvFmT4 = FvFm)

# Extract the fvfm at Timepoint 22 (last measurement)
fvfm_t22 <- df_clean %>%
  filter(Timepoint == 22) %>%
  select(UniqueID, FvFm) %>%
  rename(FvFmT22 = FvFm)

# Merge FvFmT4 and FvFmT22 back into the main dataframe
df_clean <- df_clean %>%
  left_join(fvfm_t4, by = \UniqueID\, relationship = \many-to-many\) %>%
  left_join(fvfm_t22, by = \UniqueID\, relationship = \many-to-many\)

# Add a small constant to FvFmT4 and FvFmT22 where values are 0
small_constant <- 0.0000000001

# Replace 0 values in FvFmT4 and FvFmT22 with the small constant
df_clean$FvFmT4 <- ifelse(df_clean$FvFmT4 == 0, small_constant, df_clean$FvFmT4)
df_clean$FvFmT22 <- ifelse(df_clean$FvFmT22 == 0, small_constant, df_clean$FvFmT22)

# Calculate the percent change
df_clean$PercChangeFvFm <- (df_clean$FvFmT22 - df_clean$FvFmT4) / df_clean$FvFmT4 * 100

df_clean <- df_clean %>%
  mutate(
    LogChangeFvFm = log(FvFmT22 / FvFmT4)  # Logarithmic change
  )

# Now df_clean has a new column 'PercChangeFvFm' representing the percent change in fvfm between Timepoint 4 and Timepoint 22

# Group by Treatment, Cross_2, and SymbiontTreatment, and calculate mean and standard error for percent change
log_change_fvfm_summary <- df_clean %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Cross_2, SymbiontTreatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_log_change = mean(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_log_change = sd(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
log_change_fvfm_summary <- log_change_fvfm_summary %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Define a custom color palette (same as before)
custom_colors <- c(\BxB\ = \#1f77b4\, \TxT\ = \#ff7f0e\)  # Modify colors as needed

# Plot the percent change in area with error bars and custom colors
log_change_fvfm_plot <- ggplot(log_change_fvfm_summary, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_log_change, 
                                                    color = Cross_2, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_log_change - se_log_change, ymax = mean_log_change + se_log_change), 
                width = 0.2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = \dashed\, color = \grey\) +  # Add dashed line at y = 0
  scale_color_manual(values = custom_colors) +  # Apply the custom color palette
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Log Change in Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Log Change in Larval Fv/Fm from Timepoint 4 to 22\) +
  ylim(-5, 15) +  # Adjust y-axis limits (change the values as needed)
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = \right\,
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\),  # Keep x and y axis lines
    axis.ticks = element_line(color = \black\)  # Add axis ticks
  )

# Display the plot
print(log_change_fvfm_plot)

# Create inset just for treatment
# Group by Treatment and calculate mean and standard error for percent change
log_change_summary2 <- df_clean %>%
  group_by(Treatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_log_change = mean(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_log_change = sd(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
log_change_summary2 <- log_change_summary2 %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Plot the percent change in area with error bars and custom colors
log_change_plot2 <- ggplot(log_change_summary2, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_log_change)) +
  geom_point(size = 4, shape = 1, stroke = 1.5) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_log_change - se_log_change, ymax = mean_log_change + se_log_change), 
                width = 0.2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = \dashed\, color = \grey\) +  # Add dashed line at y = 0
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Log Change in Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Log Change in Larval Fv/Fm from Timepoint 4 to 22\) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = \right\,
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\),  # Keep x and y axis lines
    axis.ticks = element_line(color = \black\)  # Add axis ticks
  )

# Display the plot
print(log_change_plot2)

# Create inset for treatment and symbiont treatment
# Group by Treatment and SymbiontTreatment, and calculate mean and standard error for percent change
log_change_summary3 <- df_clean %>%
  group_by(Treatment, SymbiontTreatment) %>%
  summarise(mean_log_change = mean(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_log_change = sd(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
log_change_summary3 <- log_change_summary3 %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Plot the percent change in area with error bars and custom colors
log_change_plot3 <- ggplot(log_change_summary3, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_log_change, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +
  geom_point(size = 4, stroke = 1.5) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_log_change - se_log_change, ymax = mean_log_change + se_log_change), 
                width = 0.2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = \dashed\, color = \grey\) +  # Add dashed line at y = 0
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Log Change in Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Log Change in Larval Fv/Fm from Timepoint 4 to 22\) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = \right\,
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\),  # Keep x and y axis lines
    axis.ticks = element_line(color = \black\)  # Add axis ticks
  )

# Display the plot
print(log_change_plot3)

library(patchwork)

# Combine the two plots side by side
combined_plot_log_fvfm <- log_change_plot2 + log_change_plot3 + plot_layout(ncol = 2)

# Display the combined plot
print(combined_plot_log_fvfm)

# Save the combined plot as a PNG file
ggsave(\combined_plot_log_fvfm_inset.png\, plot = combined_plot_log_fvfm, width = 6, height = 3, dpi = 300)

# Step 1: Filter the dataframe for larvae that survived to Timepoint 22
survived_larvae_fvfm <- df_clean %>%
  filter(FvFmT22 > 0.0000000001)

# Step 2: Calculate the log change in fvfm for the filtered data
survived_larvae_fvfm <- survived_larvae_fvfm %>%
  mutate(LogChangeFvFm = log(FvFmT22 / FvFmT4))

# Step 3: Summarize the log change for plotting
log_change_summary_survived <- survived_larvae_fvfm %>%
  group_by(Treatment, ReefMom, SymbiontTreatment, Cross_2) %>%
  summarise(mean_log_change = mean(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_log_change = sd(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
log_change_summary_survived <- log_change_summary_survived %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Ensure the Family variable is a factor (if not already)
survived_larvae_fvfm$ReefMom <- as.factor(survived_larvae_fvfm$ReefMom)

# Create custom color names for each curve
custom_curve_names <- c(\coral2\, \orange\, \darkkhaki\, \aquamarine3\, \darkred\, \darkorchid\, \blue\,\coral2\, \orange\, \darkkhaki\, \aquamarine3\, \darkred\, \darkorchid\, \blue\,\coral2\, \orange\, \darkkhaki\, \aquamarine3\, \darkred\, \darkorchid\, \blue\
)

# Plot percent change in area with colors assigned to Cross_2 and separate panels for Family
survivors_log_change <- ggplot(log_change_summary_survived, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_log_change, 
                                         color = Cross_2, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_log_change - se_log_change, ymax = mean_log_change + se_log_change), 
                width = 0.2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = \dashed\, color = \grey\) +  # Add dashed line at y = 0
  scale_color_manual(values = custom_colors) +  # Use the color palette for Cross_2
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Log Change in Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Log Change in Larval Fv/Fm (Survived to Timepoint 22)\) +
  facet_wrap(~ ReefMom, nrow = 7) +  # Create separate panels for each Family
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = \right\,  # Position of the legend
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\, linewidth = 0.5)  # Keep axis lines
  )

print(survivors_log_change)

# Save the plot to a file
ggsave(\survivors_log_change_plot.png\, 
       plot = survivors_log_change,  # Save the most recent plot
       width = 10,          # Set the width of the plot (in inches)
       height = 7,          # Set the height of the plot (in inches)
       dpi = 300)           # Set the resolution (300 dpi is good for publications)

```r
# Step 1: Filter the dataframe for larvae that survived to Timepoint 22
survived_larvae_fvfm <- df_clean %>%
  filter(FvFmT22 > 0.0000000001)

# Step 2: Calculate the log change in fvfm for the filtered data
survived_larvae_fvfm <- survived_larvae_fvfm %>%
  mutate(LogChangeFvFm = log(FvFmT22 / FvFmT4))

# Step 3: Summarize the log change for plotting
log_change_summary_survived <- survived_larvae_fvfm %>%
  group_by(Treatment, ReefMom, SymbiontTreatment, Cross_2) %>%
  summarise(mean_log_change = mean(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE),
            se_log_change = sd(LogChangeFvFm, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(n()))

# Reorder the Treatment factor in the desired order
log_change_summary_survived <- log_change_summary_survived %>%
  mutate(Treatment = factor(Treatment, levels = c(\Ambient\, \31\, \35.5\)))

# Ensure the Family variable is a factor (if not already)
survived_larvae_fvfm$ReefMom <- as.factor(survived_larvae_fvfm$ReefMom)

# Create custom color names for each curve
custom_curve_names <- c(\coral2\, \orange\, \darkkhaki\, \aquamarine3\, \darkred\, \darkorchid\, \blue\,\coral2\, \orange\, \darkkhaki\, \aquamarine3\, \darkred\, \darkorchid\, \blue\,\coral2\, \orange\, \darkkhaki\, \aquamarine3\, \darkred\, \darkorchid\, \blue\
)

# Plot percent change in area with colors assigned to Cross_2 and separate panels for Family
survivors_log_change <- ggplot(log_change_summary_survived, aes(x = Treatment, y = mean_log_change, 
                                         color = Cross_2, shape = SymbiontTreatment)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_log_change - se_log_change, ymax = mean_log_change + se_log_change), 
                width = 0.2) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = \dashed\, color = \grey\) +  # Add dashed line at y = 0
  scale_color_manual(values = custom_colors) +  # Use the color palette for Cross_2
  labs(x = \Temperature (Treatment)\, y = \Log Change in Fv/Fm ( s.e.)\,
       title = \Log Change in Larval Fv/Fm (Survived to Timepoint 22)\) +
  facet_wrap(~ ReefMom, nrow = 7) +  # Create separate panels for each Family
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = \right\,  # Position of the legend
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
    axis.line = element_line(color = \black\, linewidth = 0.5)  # Keep axis lines
  )

print(survivors_log_change)

# Save the plot to a file
ggsave(\survivors_log_change_plot.png\, 
       plot = survivors_log_change,  # Save the most recent plot
       width = 10,          # Set the width of the plot (in inches)
       height = 7,          # Set the height of the plot (in inches)
       dpi = 300)           # Set the resolution (300 dpi is good for publications)
